text: As for JNK, activated JNK phosphorylates c-Jun and other downstream substrates, enhancing their transcription activity [58] . Activated c-Jun dimerizes with other proteins such as cellular FBJ murine osteosarcoma (c-Fos) to form the activator protein 1 complex, thereby inducing genes harboring the 12-O-tetradecanoylphorbol-13-acetate (TPA) response element [59] .
